{
  "url": "https://www.qruise.com/industries/mri",
  "markdown": "[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo_qruise_light.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n  * Industries\n  * Products\n  * Resources\n  * News & Events\n  * Company\n  * [Contact](https://www.qruise.com/contact)\n  * [Docs](https://docs.qruise.com)\n\n\nMagnetic resonance\nPulse development made easy with our digital twins\n![optimal control](https://www.qruise.com/mri/optimal-control.svg)\noptimal control\nenables highly selective and robust pulse sequences\n![user friendly](https://www.qruise.com/mri/userfriendly.svg)\nuser friendly\ninterface for effortless operation\n![digital twin 1](https://www.qruise.com/mri/digitaltwin1.svg) ![digital twin 2](https://www.qruise.com/mri/digitaltwin2.svg)\ndigital twin\ntechnology creates an exact replica of your system\n![error budget](https://www.qruise.com/mri/errorbudget.svg)\nerror budget\nhighlights key sources of error\n![hardware agnostic](https://www.qruise.com/mri/hardwareagnostic.svg)\nhardware agnostic\nsoftware allows easy integration with your lab\nWhat are the challenges in magnetic resonance?\nMagnetic resonance (MR) technologies are powerful for probing physical, chemical, and biological systems. However, they continue to face challenges such as low signal sensitivity, long acquisition times, and high operational costs. All of these hinder widespread and timely use.\nDue to the complex physics involved in the spin control of MR systems, standard approaches often fail to produce spectrally and spatially precise pulses that are robust to inhomogeneities and system drift.\n![wavey](https://www.qruise.com/mri/pulse-sequence-top.svg)\n![pulsey](https://www.qruise.com/mri/pulse-sequence.svg)\nHow can Qruise help?\nOur advanced modelling tools simplify MR challenges by building a highly accurate digital twin of your system. This enables users to design and test high-fidelity, robust pulse sequences without relying on physical access to a lab or scanner. The result: accelerated development of advanced imaging and spectroscopic protocols.\nBy generating an error budget, our software identifies key sources of error - such as magnetic field fluctuations or hardware imperfections - and adapts pulses and fields in real-time through closed-loop optimisation. And all of this is seamlessly integrated into a user-friendly interface for easy operation.\nHigh-fidelity digital twins with QruiseMR\nQruiseMR packages these tools into an end-to-end solution that combines full system modelling, physics-based model learning, and advanced pulse-level optimisation to produce MR pulse sequences that have greater spectral and spatial selectivity and are more robust to fluctuations.\n![robust-pulse](https://www.qruise.com/mri/robust-pulse.png)\n[Discover QruiseMR](https://www.qruise.com/products/qruise-mr)\nQuE-MRT\nQruise is a key member of the QuE-MRT project with the aim of \u201cRevolutionising cancer imaging through quantum technologies\u201d.\nAs part of the project, we\u2019ve been developing highly selective and robust control pulse sequences that precisely target a single sample slice, minimising spin excitations in other slices for more accurate and efficient imaging.\n![mri consortium](https://www.qruise.com/mri/mri-consortium.png)\n[Find out more](https://www.quantentechnologien.de/forschung/foerderung/leuchtturmprojekte-der-quantenbasierten-messtechnik/que-mrt.html)\n[![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo-qruise-vertical.svg) ![Qruise Logo](https://www.qruise.com/logo-qruise-vertical.svg)](https://www.qruise.com/)\n  * [Company](https://www.qruise.com/company/story)\n  * [Jobs](https://qruise.jobs.personio.de/)\n  * [Blog](https://www.qruise.com/resources/blog)\n  * [Contact](https://www.qruise.com/contact)\n\n\n[](https://twitter.com/Qruise_ai) [](https://linkedin.com/company/qruise) [](https://www.youtube.com/@qruise_ai) [![bluesky profile](https://www.qruise.com/logo_bluesky.svg)](https://bsky.app/profile/qruise.bsky.social)\n\u00a9 Qruise GmbH 2026. All rights reserved\n  * [Privacy Policy](https://www.qruise.com/privacy)\n  * [Terms of Service](https://www.qruise.com/terms-and-conditions)\n  * [Imprint](https://www.qruise.com/imprint)\n\n\n![European Union flag](https://www.qruise.com/europe.svg)\nFunded by the European Union. Views and opinions expressed are however those of the author(s) only and do not necessarily reflect those of the European Union or the European Innovation Council and SMEs Execitve Agency (EISMEA). Neither the European Union nor the granting authority can be held responsible for them. Grant agreement No 101099538\n",
